The paper focuses on the design and evaluation of a clinical decision support tool, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) in the context of healthcare (cs.CY, cs.CE). The paper also discusses the importance of finding the right level of unobtrusiveness in the design of such tools, which is a key aspect of human-computer interaction (cs.HCI).
